attributes.description: Restaurant owners use undercover surveillance to spy on their employees.
attributes.name: generic-show-blueprint-page
attributes.pageMetadataDescription: Restaurant owners use undercover surveillance to spy on their employees.
attributes.title: Mystery Diners

attributes.description: Food truck teams compete to sell the most food and ultimately win $50,000.
attributes.longDescription: Each week, food truck teams roll into a new city and spend a frantic weekend competing to see which group can sell the most food. The last team standing wins the $50,000 grand prize.
attributes.name: The Great Food Truck Race

attributes.description: When top restaurants need a new executive chef, they call Anne Burrell.
attributes.longDescription: When top restaurants need to find a new executive chef, they turn to Anne Burrell. She puts four candidates through the toughest job interview of their lives and ends with the biggest test of all: running the restaurant.
attributes.name: Chef Wanted with Anne Burrell

attributes.description: Food lover Casey Webb takes on America's ultimate eating challenges.
attributes.longDescription: Food lover Casey Webb travels the country in search of America's ultimate eating challenges. From a four-pound Reuben to a gallon-sized sundae, he steps up to the table with gusto. New man, new food -- same epic battle.
attributes.name: Man v. Food

attributes.description: Robert Irvine is on a mission to find America's top aspiring restaurateur.
attributes.longDescription: This Food Network competition series hosted by Chef Robert Irvine will discover America's top aspiring restaurateur. It's the ultimate road trip where contestants face intense challenges about running restaurants.
attributes.name: Restaurant Express

attributes.description: Robert Irvine is on a mission to save failing restaurants from collapse.
attributes.longDescription: Robert Irvine is on a mission to save failing restaurants from total collapse. He and his team use all the ingenuity, elbow grease and heart they've got to give small business owners a fighting chance at turning their restaurants and their lives around.
attributes.name: Restaurant: Impossible

attributes.description: Robert Irvine takes on epic culinary tests with unbelievable obstacles.
attributes.longDescription: For each seemingly impossible mission, host Robert Irvine must cook an extraordinary meal using limited resources. From the jungles of Hawaii to the streets of Sin City, Robert battles the elements -- and the clock -- to deliver a world-class meal.
attributes.name: Dinner: Impossible

attributes.description: Chefs do anything it takes, including sabotage, to win this competition.
attributes.longDescription: Just how far is a chef willing to go win a cooking competition? Host Alton Brown hands four chefs $25,000 and the opportunity to spend that money either helping themselves or sabotaging their competitors.
attributes.name: Cutthroat Kitchen

attributes.description: Chefs, food experts and enthusiasts compete to become a Food Network Star!
attributes.longDescription: Chefs, food experts and enthusiasts compete in challenges to win their ultimate dream: a contract with Food Network and the title of Food Network Star!
attributes.name: Food Network Star

attributes.description: Gordon Ramsay helps struggling restaurants become successful.
attributes.longDescription: Gordon Ramsay visits struggling restaurants across America and spends one week trying to help them become successful.
attributes.name: Kitchen Nightmares USA

attributes.description: Chef Gordon Ramsay offers a dose of tough love to struggling restaurants.
attributes.longDescription: One of the world's best chefs, Gordon Ramsay's ability to create truly spectacular food in his restaurants is matched only by his reputation for explosive outbursts. Gordon offers a dose of his unique brand of tough love to struggling restaurants.
attributes.name: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares

attributes.description: Aspiring restaurateurs compete to run one of Gordon Ramsay's eateries.
attributes.longDescription: Celebrity chef Gordon Ramsay roasts a batch of aspiring restaurateurs as they compete against one another for an opportunity to run one of his eateries.
attributes.name: Hell's Kitchen USA

attributes.description: Store security experts steal from food businesses to reveal security flaws.
attributes.longDescription: Store security experts steal from food businesses ... all in the service of showing the owner where the security flaws are. Ultimately, they are making food businesses stronger, one heist at a time.
attributes.name: Thieves, Inc.

attributes.description: A no-nonsense fixer evaluates and revamps struggling hotels.
attributes.longDescription: No-nonsense fixer Anthony Melchiorri gets struggling hotels back on their feet and on the path to success. His management skills, emotions and patience are tested as he evaluates and revamps these down-and-out properties.
attributes.name: Hotel Impossible

attributes.description: Restaurants get help cleaning up health violations and passing inspection.
attributes.longDescription: An unexpected visit from a restaurant health inspector can shut down a food business instantly and permanently if it isn't up to code. Consultant Ben Vaughn helps restaurants clean up violations and make sure they pass inspection and stay in business.
attributes.name: Health Inspectors

attributes.description: Struggling bars face the errors of their ways in an effort to survive.
attributes.longDescription: John Green knows bars. As a top-level consultant, he's designed, staffed and launched some of the most prestigious bars and nightclubs in the world. This expert helps bars that are "on the rocks" get back into the black.
attributes.name: On The Rocks

attributes.description: Ailing hotels and resorts across America get much-needed help.
attributes.longDescription: Ailing hotels and resorts across America get much-needed help from hospitality expert Shane Green. With hidden cameras all over the properties, Shane captures every move by the hotel staff to help the resorts become top-notch.
attributes.name: Resort Rescue

attributes.description: Pastry chef Stephanie Boswell helps reinvigorate bakeries in trouble.
attributes.longDescription: Bakeries across America are failing, and struggling owners can't figure out how to save their businesses. Fortunately, award-winning pastry chef Stephanie Boswell has the sharp eye, razor wit and loving compassion to help reinvigorate beautiful bakeries.
attributes.name: Bake or Break

attributes.description: Restaurant owners use undercover surveillance to spy on their employees.
attributes.longDescription: When a restaurant owner suspects employees of not doing their jobs -- whether it be stealing, lyingor mistreating customers -- they call in the Mystery Diners to find out what's really going on when the boss isn't around.
attributes.name: Mystery Diners

attributes.description: Willie Degel helps troubled restaurants find and fix hidden problems.
attributes.longDescription: Restaurateur Willie Degel helps troubled restaurants looking to find and rectify the hidden problems that lie within their establishments. His Restaurant Stakeout secret: hidden cameras to keep a close eye on staff and patrons.
attributes.name: Restaurant Stakeout

attributes.description: A chef goes undercover to help restaurant owners on the brink of collapse.
attributes.longDescription: Restaurateur and accomplished chef Mark Estee lends his expertise to restaurant owners on the brink of failure. He poses as a customer and a member of the kitchen staff, and tensions reach a boiling point when he reveals his findings to the owners.
attributes.name: Undercover Chef

attributes.description: Hopeless cooks battle culinary challenges in hopes of winning $25,000.
attributes.longDescription: Two premier chefs work to transform a team of hopeless cooks from kitchen disasters to kitchen masters, and the last recruit standing wins $25,000.
attributes.name: Worst Cooks in America

attributes.description: Employees here threaten patrons, drink on the job and eat customers' food.
attributes.longDescription: After receiving numerous bad service reviews and noticing a 30 percent decline in revenue, the owner of Caffe boa contacts Charles Stiles and the Mystery Diners to help him find the cause of his problem.
attributes.name: F For Effort

attributes.description: "Grumpy Tom" has a knack for disrespecting everyone in The Blue Moose.
attributes.longDescription: Charles Stiles and the Mystery Diners descend upon The Blue Moose, where longtime chef "Grumpy Tom" has a knack for disrespecting everyone in the place, including the newly installed second-generation owner.
attributes.name: Grumpy Tom

attributes.description: Big Earl's Greasy Eats reports of late-night staff parties.
attributes.longDescription: After losing thousands of dollars in unaccounted alcohol and hearing rumors of late-night staff parties, the owner of Big Earl's Greasy Eats contacts Charles Stiles and the Mystery Diners for help.
attributes.name: Big Earl's Gone Wild

attributes.description: Find out how incompetent Rose's nephew is as a restaurant manager.
attributes.longDescription: Brett and Rose hire Charles Stiles and Mystery Diners Danny, Chris and Deanna to go undercover and show them just how incompetent their nephew truly is as a manager.
attributes.name: Bringing Down the Haus

attributes.description: A recently hired chef may be plotting more than just the items on the menu.
attributes.longDescription: The Groves Bar & Grill owner becomes concerned over a large loss in food and supplies, so the Mystery Diners go undercover with hidden cameras.
attributes.name: Catering on the Side

attributes.description: Mystery Diners goes undercover to see whether this brother is a keeper.
attributes.longDescription: The Mystery Diners go undercover to see what's really happening and whether this brother is a keeper.
attributes.name: Undercover Brother

attributes.description: A pub owner in LA suspects one of her bartenders might be overpouring.
attributes.longDescription: A pub owner in Los Angeles suspects that one of her bartenders might be overpouring for customers, giving away too many free drinks and overtipping himself.
attributes.name: Raiding the Bar
